rComments: Great prof, tests very closely reflect questions seen in past tests, and if you attend the lectures while asking questions, you'll most definitely succeed. Also, do the prerequisite material because it sets a great foundation for the stuff you'll learn later.

His class is very good, and he will only test you on what he taught you. Nothing not taught will be on his test. Study on his class notes, and assignments, you will get an easy A. The most important is that attending each class. Because there may be some good or important or surprise class content that may help a lot on the exam, but not recorded.

Great guy, I like that he writes out all of his notes every lecture. In his DGDs he went over the solutions for the previous assignments, midterms, and exams which really helped for the real deal. Half the time he gives bonus marks for getting a question right in his lectures. Just know tho that the course is hard since it's mostly proofs!

A solid prof and a good guy. Midterms and finals are very similar to past midterms and final. He really wants us to pass, no surprises on midterms or the final, even gave us a giant google drive folder of past midterms and finals in the beginning of the semester. Also gives bonus points for participation in live lectures (you can get up to 5%)

Professor Zaynullin was one of the best math professors I've ever had. He explains concepts very clearly and is accessible if you have any doubts. The midterms and final were challenging, but most of the questions were taken from the practice tests that he provides, with different numbers. Overall a very fair and funny professor!

He is a prof that is willing to assist you. However, the lecture is somewhat hard to understand and the lecture notes are hard to see. But the accessibility of him outside class outweigh his style of teaching during the lecture.

This professor is the best! He always answers email, always prepares you for the midterm and final exam. Lectures are the best and allows you to earn bonus points! More people should show up to his lecture! He marked the final exam IN ONE NIGHT!!!
hard to understand on his class.
Prof. Zaynullin isn't a good lecturer but his evaluations were really fair, even on the easy side. He also was always available to answer questions.
Nice guy, but I would only take this course with him. exams were easy, you have to teach yourself.

This class is a tough one. His accent is very strong and the lessons don't correspond to the tests or DGDs. Luckily, the tests stay virtually the same, and he gives you all of them from 2011. To understand the material you definitely need to participate in DGDs and get help outside of class.

Clearly more concerned with the average of his class than the students in it. Puts the exact same questions on the exams as in past exams but then marks them incorrect. Somehow aced the first two tests and failed the last. He couldn't explain the errors when asked. Didn't make much sense. Content was very easy if he were a better marker.

He's kinda confusing in lectures, the material itself can get very abstract towards the end of the semester. But the course is actually very easy to ace. All you have to do is SOLVE ALL THE PRACTICE QUESTIONS THAT HE ASSIGNS. And then you are guaranteed a good grade since the exams are literally exactly the same with the numbers changed.
I love this guy, found him hilarious. Midterms and exams are super easy as he provides many tests from previous years and the free textbook is also really good.
His name shortens to Krillin so thats kinda hype. Sometimes makes bad jokes that nobody laughs at but they amuse me.
The material he's teaching is unrelated to the textbook. The lecture notes he provided are hard to understand and only with few examples. would not recommend

Too abstract in class, doesn't answer questions very often. Hard to understand because the class is very proof heavy however the questions are straightforward. Only upside is the questions are relatively similar year to year for the course

I really enjoyed the class. Learned a lot. The material is very abstract but tests are easy and straightforward. Prof does proofs in class, however, I liked it as it gives more insight and understanding. Would not recommend it to those who hate proofs .
cant understand what hes saying. Just do te reviews and you will get a good grade

Hard class. Spends time teaching proofs rather than going over questions which is frustrating when the class is mainly graded on normal questions and not proofs. Hard to understand and isn't very receptive to questions.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Interesting guy. Spends 2 minutes teaching course material and spends the rest of the time doing proofs that I didn't understand. Study and do the tests and it should be quite easy to get a good mark as all the midterm and exam questions come from previous tests. Don't take unless you enjoy abstract proofs...
Amazing prof. Want to learn how to do proofs - take his class
The midterms are questions directly from the MapleTA assignments, so know how to do all the assignments. The final exam is NOT like the assignments but is fairly easy.
Mid terms are a lot harder than Desjardin's class. Class average is 15 percent lower than the other classes.

You can tell the prof is really into what he's teaching, but it doesn't help that the material itself is fairly abstract. If you stay on top of the assigned homework, then you won't have any problems with the assignments. Try your hardest to attend every class and DGD, and that will help. He also gives you the textbook online for free, so use it!

He's smart and lectures are alright, but sometimes skips too many steps on the board to follow (though provides complete lecture notes so you can read it later).  Assignments can be unintentionally hard (question taken from textbook) but he adjusts grading fairly afterwards.  Exams are easier than most profs.  Overall not bad, would recommend him.
Wonderful Prof ever!

MAT1320 was definitely my easiest class. Similar to gr 12 calc with intergrals. Has easy mid terms and exams. He can be a bit boring in lectures but he is one of the rare teachers where if u ask a question in class, he will answer it, even if its a stupid question. I was kind of annoyed by this yet happy about it at the same time. turtle pace

Failed with this guy last year because he was useless. He must have gotten a kick in the bum, because this year he was extremely helpful, did not mock or laugh at students, was very clear, excellent notes, etc. Very nice/smart guy. I hope he keeps up with the way he taught this year instead of going back to how he was last year.
Smart prof. Material is very abstract. However, if one attends DGDs and solves problems exams go well. Nice lecture notes. Very helpful at office hours.

Doesnt give assignments, all midterms amd finals are based on a "problem list" he updates throughout semester(almost all answers can be googled). he doesnt understand what people are asking when they have questions. he mocks students when they ask questions (ie. he laughs at us). dont take this class with him if you have a choice!!!

This is a very abstract course, and is very hard to understand for a lot of people, and he doesn't make it any easier. His exams are all exact problems taken from the problem list, so if you understand the problems, you should be find. He gives some answers in the DGD, and will help you in office hours, but it's not easy to do well in the class.

Nice and smart guy, but teaches in a way that is inconsistent with every other professor.  I wouldn't fault him for the abstractness, as that seems to just be the nature of the course.  But as the other rater said, he doesn't give actual assignments - just updates a "problem list" with a TON of problems from the book at random intervals.

He's a very nice guy, but his lectures are absolute garbage. He teaches the material in a way that's way too abstract for the class to understand, and his DGDs, which are supposed to be dumbed down, are just as abstract. There aren't any assignments, but this gives no reason to do any actual work. He's also incredibly boring to listen to...

well, although this professor does not explain the stuff clearly, he has SUPER EASY exams. JUST STUDY HIS PREPARATION TESTS and make sure that you solve ALL of them. I guarantee that you will take A+++ if you do what I said. DO NOT ALSO FORGET TO ATTEND THE DGDs or SOLVE THEIR QUESTIONS. his exams are straightforward

Took Linear Algebra with the prof...his teaching is a little abstract and that can be confusing for few but his midterm and final is really easy. There were no assignments. Use the textbook and youtube and you can ace the course with this guy.
